# RollyCast environment variables (example)
#
# Local development and unit/integration tests require NONE of these — the worker
# runs on Miniflare via `wrangler dev` and needs no cloud account.
#
# These matter only for a LIVE Cloudflare deploy (`wrangler deploy`).

# --- Client (apps/web, Vite) ---
# WebSocket/host origin the client connects to. Leave empty in dev to use the
# Vite dev proxy (same origin). In production the client and worker share one
# origin, so this is usually left blank.
VITE_PUBLIC_PARTY_HOST=

# --- Worker (apps/worker) deploy ---
# Set via `wrangler login` (preferred) or a scoped API token in CI:
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=
